e Crying of Lot 49 in which the road from Argos to Athens, built to differentiate a human domain from the undefined outside, has become a Los Angeles freeway desecrating the land and its people in a predatory urban sprawl.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aGreek drama (Tragedy)xHistory and criticism. 0aPolitical plays, GreekxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitical sciencezGreece. 0aPolitics and literaturezGreece. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAchilles.  aAntigone.  aApollo.  aArrowsmith, W.  aBacon, H.  aBové, P.  aConnor, W. R.  aDionysus.  aEpidamnus.  aFinley, J. H.  aFoucault, M.  aGadamer, H. G.  aGoldhill, S.  aHabermas, J.  aHolmes, S. T.  aIgnatieff, M.  aKitto, H.D.F.  aKnox, B.  aKundera, M.  aLamb, W.R.M.  aLoraux, N.  aMarx, K.  aNietzsche, F.  aNussbaum, M.  aOedipus.  aPentheus.  aSaxonhouse, A.  aSocrates.  achoice.  acorruption.  adeinos.  ademocracy.  aelenchus.  aentropy.  aexile.  aheroic ethic.  aidentity.  ajustice: in Oresteia.  amethodism, criticism of.  amodernity.  anarcissism, in Pynchon.  apaternalism.  apleonexia.  areconciliation.  asuffering.  atheoretical moment.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Gap Yearsz978311078423740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691218182?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691218182423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691218182/original  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  a978-3-11-078423-7  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Gap Years  aEBA_BA